message: Expanded his political trayectory, with aid of his official public curriculum published in the webpage of the Chamber of Deputies
Expanded the information box and corrected the numeration of his governor-ship.
Added a link for the Mexican Congress of the Union

Corrected his alma mater and complemented the information with what is available on the Spanish version, since there are more sources about him in Spanish. I'm not done in that regard, and I'll continue adding information eventually. (I'm using the citations included in the Spanish version, obviously checking them beforehand to see if the information is accurate, but I'm not using the Spanish wikipedia page itself as a source)
Carlos Miguel Aysa González is no longer acting governor of Campeche.

Readded information about Hank Rhon's son: Carlos Hank Gonzalez. Yes, he shares a name with his grandfather. Yes, it is confusing, but I've added a direct link to his son's wikipedia page (not as a citation) to try to help with any ambiguity that may come from it. I had added this before, so there was no good reason to remove it.
Expanded on recent developments of his term as president of the PRI

Removed defamatory information. The sources cited clearly state the reports were dismissed by the same authorities that presented it. A lot of the information presented was also factually wrong, such as the smuggling the Siberian Tiger, which by the cited source was brought by Jorge Hank Rhon, not Carlos. Additionally, Jorge Hank Rhon is not Carlos' son, he's his sibling. Remember, names in Mexico have two surnames, a paternal surname and a maternal surname.
Corrected a difference. The party is still called Movement for National Regeneration. MORENA is an acronym.
Readded the factual difference expansion with the right citation
Added a section for controversies about the National Guard
Complemented reception with audience scores and expanded factual differences
Added information and citation for the transfer of the National Guard to the Mexican Army.
missed a typo on a different segment
Changed biased reporting in a segment
brought an earlier version that appears to be more complete and less arbitrary.
Restored to the original version including the defamations and in popular culture sections.

message: Added relevant information to the mining section.

Undid revision 1073186875 by [[Special:Contributions/Udonknome|Udonknome]] ([[User talk:Udonknome|talk]]) there are no court rulings confirming the allegations included in the profile. Hank was never prosecuted or sentenced by any judge, so it is a defamation to claim that he is a "criminal" or to refer to links with organized crime.
Writing and updating information using WSJ, AP News and LA Times as sources.

Removed defamatory and unprecise information. Just because there is a citation, it does not necessarily mean information is not defamatory. By the very sources cited on the edit, the White Tiger report was disavowed by the DOJ, as it had been leaked and not properly vetted. The geopolitical drug watch was not speaking about the Hank family (read your source properly). I don't want to assume bad faith but it's the second time the information is presented incompletely, at best.
